Trivia
The Huey Lewis and the News song &quot;Hip to Be Square&quot;, which appears in the film, was initially on the soundtrack album, but it was removed shortly after release because of a lack of publishing rights. The album was recalled and reissued without the song, although some versions of the initial batch had already sold. Over the years, this incident has developed into the myth that Huey Lewis himself refused to allow the song on the album due to the content of the movie. 

Goofs
Patrick pronounces &quot;Robert Palmer&quot; as &quot;Robert Parmer&quot;, revealing a flaw in Christian Bale's staged American accent. 

